               <p>JOHN JONES. I am <rs id="t18270913-330-viclabel1840" type="occupation">clerk</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-330-victim2442 t18270913-330-viclabel1840"></join> to Mr. Goss. About nine o'clock in the morning I passed three lads just by the Fleet-prison, standing with their backs against the wall - they followed me till I got near the <placeName id="t18270913-330-crimeloc1841">Old Bailey, on Ludgate-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-330-crimeloc1841" type="placeName" value="Old Bailey, on Ludgate-hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-330-crimeloc1841" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-330-off1838 t18270913-330-crimeloc1841"></join>. I felt something touch my heel - I turned and saw the prisoner with my handkerchief inside his coat, under his arm - he ran across the street. I followed calling Stop thief! - he threw it down - I took it up, and he was taken- it was safe a minute before.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. J. ALLEY. Q. Did the others appear in his company? A. Yes - I believe they spoke together. I do not know what became of the others.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-330-person2443">
                  ALEXANDER 
                  JOHNSON
